prompt:
Add a public function called ApplyDouble to Calculator.calr that takes an i32 parameter and applies a doubling lambda to it. Use inline arrow lambda syntax.

Use this exact Calor inline lambda syntax:
§F{f003:ApplyDouble:pub}
  §I{i32:x}
  §O{i32}
  §B{doubler} (n) → (* n 2)
  §R §C{doubler}
    §A x
  §/C
§/F{f003}

The (param) → expr syntax creates an inline lambda:
- (n) → (* n 2) is a lambda that doubles its input
- Multiple params: (a, b) → (+ a b)
- Can be bound to a variable and called later
